Parameter: loyalty_command
Definition: How far the people under or around the character are willing to go for them. This measures real devotion and obedience — not formal rank, not authority scope, not fear-based compliance that collapses under pressure. A king whose subjects would betray him instantly scores low. A nobody whose friends would die for them scores high.

Tier calibration (pseudo-characters as lower boundaries):
[T1]  A person whose followers abandon them at the first sign of trouble.
[T2]  A person with reliable allies whose commitment has clear limits.
[T3]  A person who inspires genuine dedication. Followers endure significant hardship.
[T4]  A person whose followers sacrifice their lives without hesitation on their word.
[T5]  A person whose followers act against self-preservation, logic, or morality out of devotion.
[T6]  A person whose devotion persists across generations, reshapes civilizations, or alters followers' bodies, minds, or souls.
[T7]  A being whose followers' loyalty transcends death, time, and the boundaries of their fictional universe.

Return JSON:
{"universe": "{{ universe }}", "parameter": "loyalty_command", "sorted": ["T1", ..., "T7"], "unknown": [...]}

All 7 markers T1..T7 must appear in sorted, in order.

